com.gembox.spreadsheet.internal.styles

Class AbstractStyleHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gembox.spreadsheet.internal.styles.AbstractStyleHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AlignmentDataFormatHandler, BorderHandler, CellFormatDataFormatHandler, FillDataFormatHandler, FontDataFormatHandler, FormatHandler, NumberDataFormatHandler, ProtectionDataFormatHandler, StyleHandler
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ColumnRowCellStyleHandler, DifferentialStyleHandler, NewStyleHandler, OdsStyleHandler, RangeStyleHandler, StyleHandlerImpl

    public abstract class AbstractStyleHandler
extends Object
implements NumberDataFormatHandler, StyleHandler, AlignmentDataFormatHandler, FontDataFormatHandler, BorderHandler, FillDataFormatHandler, ProtectionDataFormatHandler
    Represents a base style handler for all non-differential styles: column / row / cell / cell range style, (named) style and style created from public constructor.

    This type also implements handlers for all formatting groups (number, alignment, font, border, fill and protection) to reduce number of types, avoid deep compositions of types and increase performance. SRP (single-responsibility-principle) is sacrificed for simplicity and performance.

    Type is partial and implementation and interface for each formatting is in its own file.

      • getStyles

        protected abstract CellStyleCollection getStyles()
        Gets the styles associated with the workbook to which this style handler belongs.

        This member is required because it provides additional services required by format handlers, like importing style (if it is from another workbook), caching, retrieving color scheme, default / empty formatting and default ('Normal') style.

        Returns:
        The styles associated with the workbook to which this style handler belongs.

      • getCellFormatHolder

        protected abstract CellFormatDataFormatHolder getCellFormatHolder()
        Gets the cell format holder.

        Cell format holder is usually a parent editor (ExcelColumnRowBase or ExcelCell) of this cell format handler which either stores or inherits cell formatting.

        For example, ExcelCell can either have cell formatting directly in its data, if it is allocated; otherwise it will inherit cell formatting from either ExcelRow or ExcelColumn or default / empty formatting from the associated workbook.

        Returns:
        The cell format holder.

      • isDifferential

        public boolean isDifferential()
        Gets a value indicating whether formatting is differential.

        If formatting is differential, then editor should always set some concrete value in {T}.Set(Action{T}) method; otherwise, it can set null if value is default.

        For example, if setting FontData.getItalic() and formatting is differential, only true or false value should be set. If formatting is not differential, then instead of false value, null can be set.

        Differential formatting inherits properties which are not null. Differential formatting are currently not used in GemBox.Spreadsheet, but they might soon be used (if we add support for rich text, rich text comments, conditional formatting, tables, pivot tables, auto-filter, sorting, etc.)

        Specified by:
        isDifferential in interface FormatHandler
        Returns:
        true if formatting is differential; otherwise, false.

      • getColors

        public final ColorScheme getColors()
        Gets the color scheme associated with this format handler.

        Color scheme is used to convert theme and indexed (palette) colors to RGB format.

        If format handler is not associated with any workbook, then default color scheme is used (default 'Office' theme and default color palette); otherwise, color scheme from the associated workbook is used.

        Specified by:
        getColors in interface FormatHandler

      • setCellFormat

        public void setCellFormat(CellFormatData value)
        Sets the cell formatting.

        Input cell formatting can be null, in which case it is replaced with empty formatting associated with the handler's workbook (default cell formatting which inherits all from 'Normal' style).

        If input cell formatting is from the another workbook or it is not attached to any workbook, it is imported.

        Input cell formatting is either cached / frozen or cloned (modifying it later won't make any changes in the underlying storage).

        Parameters:
        value - The cell formatting.

      • setCellFormat

        public void setCellFormat(CellFormatData value,
                          EnumSet<CellFormatFlags> flags)
        Sets the cell formatting with specific formatting flags. If formatting flag is off, value will include formatting from the underlying format holder.

        Input cell formatting can be null, in which case it is replaced with empty formatting associated with the handler's workbook (default cell formatting which inherits all from 'Normal' style).

        If input cell formatting is from the another workbook or it is not attached to any workbook, it is imported.

        Input cell formatting is either cached / frozen or cloned (modifying it later won't make any changes in the underlying storage).

        Parameters:
        value - The cell formatting value.
        flags - The cell formatting flags.
